{{see|keks}}
==German==

===Etymology===
Originally called {{E.}} ''[[cake]]s'' by Hermann Bahlsen, who brought the idea to Germany in 1889. From 1911 his company changed the name of the article to ''Keks'', back then the plural was ''Keks'' too.

===Noun===
'''Keks''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''Kekse''')
# a [[cookie]]

